        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel explosive gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes, or other ignition
                        sources away at all times. Alway wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near
                        batteries to prevent personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0008081">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0008082">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the battery cable from the negative terminal.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Route and secure the dimmer switch relay harness to the main cab harness
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008081">(Figure 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the relay harness 3/8 inch eyelet to the cab ground on the driver's side
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008081">(Item 4, Figure 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect dimmer switch connector 42 (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008082">Figure 2</hotlnk>) on the vehicle and connect the dimmer switch connector
                    to the dimmer switch lead on the relay harness (Item 2, Figure 1). Connect the other end of the
                    dimmer switch lead from the cab harness to the remaining dimmer switch connector on the relay
                    harness
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008081">(Item 3, Figure 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove circuit 50B
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008082">(Figure 2)</hotlnk>
                    from the headlight switch connector 465
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008082">(Figure 2</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008081">Item 5, Figure 1)</hotlnk>, cut off the terminal and replace with terminal
                    Part Number 1661220C1. Insert the wire with new terminal end into the headlight enable cap (single
                    cavity connector provided on the dimmer switch harness) and re-connect the connector to the dimmer
                    switch relay harness
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008081">(Item 6, Figure 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert headlight switch terminal (circuits 50BA and 50B) on the dimmer switch harness
                    into cavity 6 on the headlight switch connector 465 (same location where 50B was removed from)
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008081">(Item 5, Figure 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the dimmer switch relay connector to any open position on the fuse panel and
                    install the relay into the connector
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0008081">(Item 7, Figure 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Identify the dimmer switch relay position on the fuse label on the back of the glove
                    box.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-connect the cable to the negative battery terminal.</para>
            </step1>
